Comment: 10,0:02:56.81,0:02:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Sign,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:11.56,0:00:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Melos! Wait, Melos!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:18.79,0:00:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened? \NYou dashed away so suddenly.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:21.83,0:00:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's because I could see the town of Liaon. {ライアンの街 - if I'm not mistaken, it's not in any over versions of hashire melos, here they called the country this happens in "Raian" for some reason: Country of ... / Town of ... / King of ...; "raian" doesn't mean anything by itself in Japanese, but since this is a movie for children, it could be a portmanteau of "rai" (lightning) and "an" (darkness), or maybe I'm just overthinking}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:25.08,0:00:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Our village is beyond that town and\N the mountain behind it. Right, Friend? {yes, that's literally his name; remember I said it's a movie for children}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:29.26,0:00:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:37.93,0:00:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If we walk two more days, \Nwe'll be there.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.19,0:00:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet Nina is waiting for us eagerly.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:42.98,0:00:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course she is. The wedding can't start until you're back.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:49.36,0:00:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for everything. \NI owe you one.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:52.96,0:00:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Friend. \NLet me carry it now.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:55.25,0:00:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your precious little sister's bridal gown,\N so take good care of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:59.31,0:01:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. You really saved me\N by tagging along.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:01.58,0:01:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on, now. \NIt's not even worth mentioning.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:04.11,0:01:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Executions!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:05.42,0:01:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Five more today!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:07.95,0:01:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that about?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:09.73,0:01:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They kill the innocent!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:11.71,0:01:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Executions!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:27.82,0:01:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor girls...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:29.21,0:01:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What cruelty!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:32.09,0:01:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, the gods save us all.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:33.36,0:01:36.05,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Mister, what did those women do?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:36.05,0:01:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven't done anything.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:37.71,0:01:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet they'll receive capital punishment for no crime.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:40.55,0:01:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So they haven't done anything?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:42.65,0:01:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why execute them, then?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:44.18,0:01:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the king's order.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:46.39,0:01:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This king of the Liaon Empire \Nsees treason everywhere.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:50.46,0:01:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All who even dare to gossip about him \Nreceive capital punishment.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:55.76,0:01:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How can he be that cruel? \NI'll see the king and stop him!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:58.85,0:02:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Melos!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:00.49,0:02:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You go there, and then what? \NRelax! Give it a rest, Melos!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:03.66,0:02:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:04.83,0:02:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.33,0:02:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:14.98,0:02:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.16,0:02:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't do that!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:20.86,0:02:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.98,0:02:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Give Mom back!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:26.55,0:02:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me back my mom!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.96,0:02:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I definitely must stop them!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:30.69,0:02:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos, stop! Calm down, Melos!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:36.83,0:02:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.45,0:02:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the King of Liaon!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.39,0:02:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you interfere with the executions?!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:44.91,0:02:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I never forgive those who disobey me!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.03,0:02:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you interfere?! Answer me!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:51.03,0:02:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,King!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:52.29,0:02:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you killing innocent people?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.73,0:02:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you distrust everyone?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.99,0:03:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do I distrust them?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.83,0:03:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Because humans are a treacherous breed! {lit: people can't be trusted or something}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.49,0:03:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I distrust them because \NI can't believe them! That's all!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:06.76,0:03:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And I kill those I can't trust!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:09.19,0:03:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is more embarrassing than distrusting the hearts of others!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.61,0:03:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up! Shut up!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.38,0:03:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,King... Why are you like that?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.36,0:03:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up! Don't you know \Nwhat "shut up" means?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:22.41,0:03:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans can't live \Nwithout trusting each other.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.58,0:03:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If the king believes in his people, \Nthe people will believe in the king!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:30.35,0:03:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You can pay lip service \Nto those ideals all you want! {lit: only in words, you can even say beautiful things}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.41,0:03:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But deep down, everyone's heart is corrupt.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:36.45,0:03:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours too, just like those\N in this morning's execution lineup!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.59,0:03:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not like that, King!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:44.45,0:03:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And a liar too! At least try to come up \Nwith something more plausible.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.09,0:03:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're on the cross, \Na tearful apology will be of no use!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.59,0:03:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to apologize,\N now's the time!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.16,0:03:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm {\i1}not{\i0} going to apologize!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.73,0:03:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting. Take him away!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.48,0:03:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:11.61,0:04:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.05,0:04:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you waiting for? \NThrow him into a cell!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.66,0:04:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.20,0:04:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Move it!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:18.73,0:04:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,King...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.01,0:04:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,King, if I may ask, \Nplease give me just a day.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:23.79,0:04:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I implore you to stay my execution for just a day!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.35,0:04:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I absolutely need to see my sister first \Nand give her this wedding dress.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:31.03,0:04:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Not happening!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.15,0:04:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg you, King!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:34.06,0:04:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,My sister is waiting for my return\Nbeyond the nearest mountain.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:37.23,0:04:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I will see her once \Nand then come right back!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.79,0:04:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg you!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.19,0:04:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Like hell I'd allow that, you fraud!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.96,0:04:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't trust anyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.56,0:04:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Who'd be dumb enough to come back to die when given a chance to run for the hills?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:51.69,0:04:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never let you play me!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.61,0:04:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,King, please let him go.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.05,0:05:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,King, I will be Melos's stand-in.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.96,0:05:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be your hostage \Nuntil Melos comes back.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.09,0:05:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Friend?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.46,0:05:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Should Melos fail to come back, \Nthen I'll humbly accept the death penalty.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.79,0:05:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, King.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.52,0:05:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,King, please.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.41,0:05:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I like it. You're willing to sacrifice yourself for your friend's sake?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.52,0:05:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.29,0:05:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true? Thank you, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.03,0:05:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Friend, no! You can't stand in for me!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:33.05,0:05:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos, you just need to give this\N to your sister, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.65,0:05:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You two are the only children in your family, \Nso you must go, Melos. Go now!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:49.08,0:05:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Friend...{resume TC}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.92,0:06:21.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right! Be back by sunset \Nthe day after tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.29,0:06:25.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,The belfry bells chime\N five times at sunset. {lit: church bells - I wonder what kind of church with bells it was in 400 b.c. lol}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.16,0:06:30.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,If you're not back by the time the bells stop chiming, {your friend }Friend will lose his life!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.43,0:06:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.29,0:07:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:45.79,0:07:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nina!{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.19,0:07:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nina! {\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.59,0:07:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.53,0:08:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Melos.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.59,0:08:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're beautiful, Nina.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:26.90,0:08:27.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.88,0:08:34.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,If you're not back by the time the belfry bells chime five times, Friend will die!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:40.63,0:08:42.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,Friend, wait for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:42.89,0:08:44.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,I will surely come back!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.26,0:08:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Melos? \NMelos! Where are you going?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.98,0:09:01.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,Nina, live on and be happy!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.26,0:09:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos! Don't go, Melos! {hear "hike" (withdraw), but could be "ike" (go)}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.90,0:09:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If you value your life, \Nyou don't have to come back.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.13,0:09:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That way you will be saved. \NDon't you value your life?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:47.95,0:09:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos, why are you hesitating?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:50.96,0:09:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If you value your life at all, \Nwhy bother coming back?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:55.69,0:09:57.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,I can't run as fast as I want in this rain.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.79,0:10:00.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's hopeless! \NThere's no way I can return in time!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:00.73,0:10:03.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,If I can't get there in time, \NI might as well turn back now.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.66,0:10:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos, you just need to give this\N to your sister, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.19,0:10:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You two are the only children in your family, \Nso you must go, Melos.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.06,0:10:43.85,Thought,,0,0,0,,I made a promise. Friend believed in me \Nand volunteered to stand in for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:18.49,0:11:20.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,Friend... Here I come!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.13,0:12:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The hour of reckoning\N is almost upon us. {lit: there's only little time left until the promised time}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:02.40,0:12:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Melos, whom you believed in, will really come.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.33,0:12:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you believe \Nin your friend is up to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.66,0:12:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't see why Melos\N would come back.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:14.06,0:12:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If he doesn't make it in time, you'll die!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.32,0:12:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If he wanted to save you, \Nhe'd be here by now.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:21.63,0:12:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But Melos won't come back! \NWhy would he come back just to get killed?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:25.53,0:12:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare for an execution!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.39,0:12:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.86,0:12:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason for Melos to return?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.66,0:12:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying Melos betrayed me?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:33.29,0:12:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But if Melos doesn't come... \NIf he doesn't come...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.83,0:12:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,King, I... I...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.69,0:12:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you looking that pale now?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:45.19,0:12:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You must have started doubting \Nthat Melos would come back too!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:48.98,0:12:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. Get on your knees \Nand beg for my pardon!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.26,0:12:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Admit that friendship is but an illusion!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.46,0:12:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All who trust others are fools!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.26,0:13:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonsense! Melos will come. \NI know he will!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:06.76,0:13:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos will surely be back. \NI believe in Melos!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.82,0:13:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:27.89,0:13:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.09,0:13:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a dream?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.53,0:13:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! I've completely lost track of time.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:01.53,0:14:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The sun... The sun is setting!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:23.99,0:14:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Friend, no matter how long we wait, \NMelos won't come!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.08,0:14:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos played you. He betrayed you!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:30.23,0:14:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Believing in others is utter folly!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:34.33,0:14:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let your death be a lesson to everyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.72,0:14:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What is Melos doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.39,0:14:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor fellow. \NAnother one will lose his life today.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.42,0:14:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up already. The sun has almost set! \NAnd when it does, the bells will start chiming.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.19,0:14:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,After the fifth chime, you'll die!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.93,0:15:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.03,0:15:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He's here!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.96,0:15:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Melos!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:39.09,0:15:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He came back!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.18,0:15:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see him too! {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.73,0:15:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Melos! Melos is back!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:55.23,0:15:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.99,0:15:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.55,0:15:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He really is back! {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.83,0:16:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank the gods! {yokatta?}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.76,0:16:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, King! \NIf you're going to kill, kill me!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.49,0:16:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How is this possible?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.46,0:16:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.99,0:16:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Melos!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.06,0:16:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Friend!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.19,0:16:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Friend...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.23,0:16:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Friend...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:26.39,0:16:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hit me as hard as you can.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.86,0:16:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I was about to give up on returning. \NI was about to betray you!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.49,0:16:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos, please forgive me. \NI doubted you in my heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.59,0:16:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't sure you were\N going to come back.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.16,0:16:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Friend!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.33,0:16:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Melos!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.09,0:16:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.06,0:17:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You two trusted each other \Nfrom the bottom of your hearts.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.89,0:17:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I see now. I was wrong.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:34.98,0:17:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank the gods! \NThe king will stop killing people!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.69,0:17:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.92,0:17:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You did well!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.76,0:17:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Friend!
